text: Josefa Vila Betancur (born 6 February 1997) is a Chilean rower. She competed in the women's lightweight double sculls event at the 2016 Summer Olympics. Vila is a business engineering student at the Federico Santa María Technical University in Valparaíso. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Chilean female rowers Category:Olympic rowers of Chile Category:Rowers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Concepción, Chile Category:Rowers at the 2015 Pan American Games Category:South American Games bronze medalists for Chile Category:South American Games medalists in rowing Category:Competitors at the 2014 South American Games
